(pbh/vqpr) is the only entry point to bhutan by air. it is located in the south west of the country and served only by the country's flag carrier druk air [11]. e-tickets have been in use since april 1st 2008. druk operates four planes (three airbuses and an atr-42) which fly routes to bangkok in thailand; delhi, kolkata, bodhgaya/ gaya, bagdogra, guwahati in india; kathmandu in nepal; dhaka in bangladesh. there are two domestic airports. yongphulla airport is located in trashigang in the east and bathpalathang airport is located at jakar in the bumthang district - however both of these 